overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  agent meticulously analyzed the existing implementation against these
  documents, identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent
  proceeded to implement these missing features. Key additions included a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores.
  Detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome was integrated, along with tailored
  recommendations. The scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) was
  enhanced with a weighted system. Furthermore, the CSV export functionality was
  expanded to include all questionnaire data, and new questions were introduced
  to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue symptoms, including a warning
  for potential chronic fatigue syndrome. The agent maintained a structured
  workflow, addressing each task sequentially and ensuring code quality through
  regular lint checks.
